HEADWORD: Links
<hw>Links</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧⟦nsm⟧ks)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[The pl.
form of <er>Link</er>, but often construed as a singular.]</ety> <def>A
tract of ground laid out for the game of golf; a golfing
green.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A second <qex>links</qex> has recently been opened at Prestwick,
and another at Troon, on the same coast.</q> <rj><qau>P. P.
Alexander.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

